{
  "texts": [
    "Therefore, healthcare experts will be unable to understand the basis of the answers from the HFM, having significant concern about ethics and safety.",
    "b) Fairness [395] is another aspect of the responsibility.",
    "Due to the distribution bias in the training dataset, HFM may be susceptible to inherent biases from the dataset, breaking the fairness of the outcome.",
    "Some work has unearthed pervasive biases and stereotypes in LFMs [396], [397].",
    "This is dangerous, as unfair predictions may increase potential discrimination and undermine the equality of human life in healthcare, triggering potential social conflicts."
  ]
}